content: As an AI language model, I don't have access to current data about how well other singing competitions support their winners and finalists. However, it is believed that other singing competitions such as The Voice and America's Got Talent have also had mixed success in helping contestants transition into successful post-show careers. Some winners and runners-up have gone on to enjoy continued success in the music industry, while others have struggled to find their footing. Ultimately, the music industry is notoriously difficult to break into, and achieving long-term success as an artist requires not just talent, but also marketing savvy, industry connections, and a bit of luck.
